===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the bronze script it is a {{Han compound|厂|殳|c1=p|c2=s|ls=psc|ls2=ic|nocap=y}}, showing a hammer in hand breaking a stone with fragments coming off ({{zh-ref|Li Xueqin, 2012}}); 殳 was the pictogram of a hammer and later was borrowed to indicate a bamboo halberd. Most of the character is identical to [[叚]].

